export default (cb, obj) =>
  Array.isArray(obj)
    ? obj.filter(i => !cb(i))
    : Object.keys(obj).reduce((res, cur) => {
      if (!cb(obj[cur])) res[cur] = obj[cur]
      return res
    }, {})

export default (cb, obj) =>
  Array.isArray(obj)
    ? obj.filter(i => !cb(i))
    : Object.keys(obj).reduce((res, cur) => {
      if (!cb(obj[cur])) res[cur] = obj[cur]
      return res
    }, {})

  Array.isArray(obj)

      return res
    }, {})

import mean from '../mean'

const median = (list) => {
  var width = 2 - list.length % 2
  var idx = (list.length - width) / 2
  return !list.length
    ? NaN
    : mean(
      list.slice()
        .sort((a, b) => a < b ? -1 : a > b ? 1 : 0)
        .slice(idx, idx + width)
    )
}

export default median
